subSubSection.paragraph:
Description:
Carapace globular with LV overlapping RV ventrally (
Fig. 6E
). In lateral view, dorsal margin strongly arched with maximum height at mid-length, anterior margin slightly more inflated than posterior margin, ventral margin slightly concave. In dorsal view egg-shaped, with maximum width posterior of mid-length, posterior margin more rounded than anterior margin, anteriorly with LV overlapping RV (
Fig. 6A
). Central-dorsal to centralventral part of carapace surface pitted, grading to longitudinal lines in central ventral area (
Fig. 6B
). Both valves with ventral outer lists, LV list extending to antero-dorsal area. LV calcified inner lamella wide in postero-ventral area and with list close to inner edge of inner lamella, grading to groove along ventral area and back to list on anterior calcified inner lamella (
Fig. 6C
). RV with inner list on postero-ventral area, and slight list in antero-ventral area (
Fig. 6D
). Septa present along RV anterior and postero-ventral margins (
Fig. 6F
). LV with short, weakly developed septa along anterior and postero-ventral margins, not reaching inner edge of calcified inner lamella (
Fig. 6G
).
